caption: This particular location has managed getting drinks out orderly and I want to give them props for the 3 + times I found it worthwhile walking away from the Roscoe and southport location's order free-for-all this year.
This Starbucks has friendly people, but their employees can change often. I also experienced my orders being wrong now and then.

Very good store on Lincoln in Chicago.  This is a smaller space with seating for around 15 people.  They have the usual items that you can purchase to eat or drink and a selection of gifts and take home items.  The staff was very friendly and greeted us as we walked in and as we left the store.

Great to be able to hang out in a Starbucks. Tables were very well spaced. It was a little cool and breezy. They probably had the fan on continuous for max ventilation which is a good thing. Coffee was good. Great location.

I have lived in the neighborhood for four years now.  This management and staff are without a doubt, the kindest, warmest, and competent I have ever encountered.  This group goes above and beyond consistently.  They represent the very best of the Starbucks brand.

Cant say enough good things about this location. Drinks come out quick, staff friendly and knowledgeable and the cream station is always stocked up with what ever i need to customize my drip coffee. Management is diligent as well as welcoming and it shows thru the behavior of the counter people. Music is always on point. Love the location just off of the Paulina stop. Stop in, make some friends, you wont be disappointed.

All the baristas I've encountered were talkative and friendly which is why I stop by on my way to work.
